## 🧪 Testing

### Escrow Testing
- Cross-chain escrow locking correctness
- Escrow verification via oracle + light client
- Escrow timeout and refund
- Escrow dispute resolution
- Escrow extension (mutual agreement)

### Atomic Settlement Testing
- HTLC-based settlement correctness (happy path)
- Two-phase commit correctness (happy path)
- Atomicity under normal conditions (both settle)
- Atomicity under failure conditions (both refund)
- No partial state under any failure scenario

### Chaos Testing
- Network partition: trade survives or refunds correctly
- Chain reorg: lock proof remains valid or trade cancels
- Timeout race: no funds stuck
- Byzantine validators: invalid state rejected
- Oracle failure: fallback to light client works

### Test Coverage Goals
- Escrow: >95%
- Atomic settlement: >95%
- Chaos scenarios: >90%

